You are not allowed to redistribute my map unless you have my permission. Doing so will cause the ban of your account.

I know there is no displacements but it is my first CS:S map and it's a large step in mapping from my other maps. This map is mostly filled with wacky and weird things. Explore, take your time. Just don't get sucked in the map's aurora of fads.

It features:

- Bump Maps
- 1 Cube Map (hold on I'm not a detail extremist :P)
- 3 background songs. Each one has a 33% chance of playing on 1 round
- A dusk-like time zone for a war feeling
- An anti-terrorist and anti-counter-terrorist shotgun of light in the middle, which activates in about 45 seconds
- AWESOME CUSTOM TEXTURES from TopHATTwaffle and me
- Funny deaths and sounds
- A nice machine gun sound in the background for a feeling of distance
- and MORE!!!


Known bugs:
- The teleport effect of when you touch the Justin Bieber picture might glitch you in midair. Sorry, I haven't found a fix for it.
- There may be more, but I can't find anything else.

P.M for help and bug reports.

Alrighty then, well, this map is primarily an experiment with making every visible surface to be a displacement with the exception of the water. Anyway, this is supposed to be located near where de_dust and de_dust2 take place. Maybe not, who knows really. But either way, this is supposed to be some sort of rock quarry in the middle-east,. It gets to be a lot of fun when you play with a full server. What usually happens is that everyone goes toward the center, a few deaths occur and people from either side begin to back out of the fight and hide behind one of the rock platforms or in one of the caves. Then that's where it gets interesting. What's really fun to do is to get an opponent to start chasing you, then one of your team-mates starts to chase them, and vice versa until it begins to look like the Boston Marathon. So special features; for one, it has HDR which is a nice feature to have, especially in desert map. A 3D skybox is something that a lot of people like apparently, so I added that. There is even an easter egg. What is it? Well, look up at where the fences are, look to where a gap is; there's a man standing there watching the whole fight. He's not static, watch him, he'll shift a bit. Anyway, I hope you'll enjoy this map, I know you will. If not gameplay, then visually. EDIT: As a side-note the caves are supposed to lack lighting. So do not downvote something that was intentional.

This is more than just a Knife arena, it's who ever survives last! This map was designed to kill off thoes people that always run from you, almost everything is breakable and you will die if its by a person, spikes, fire, or you just ran out of time. The map will start everyone caged up for atleast 3 seconds, 30 seconds later the spikes will open up and try to force you into them, if thats not enough fires will spread threwout the map while people try to kill you. If you survive that far there will be a sceries of lasers that will pass threw, by then you should be about dead and ready for the next round. If you are the last one you will get 30 seconds to kill the last person before the floor opens up and kills everyone off... you will die, no matter what.

Small CS:S Map

I wanted to try my hand at making a map that took full advantage of HDR and a sun to boot. It features two cranes that are connected by two wooden planks. The top of the crane and the catwalk are the two chokepoints. You can also lure your foe into spawn and sneak up on them. So yeah, the skybox may not be the best, but come on, I managed to line up the cranes in the playfield with the continuation in the skybox. The construction took last night and a couple of added hours today to decide and add visuals. Sorry if the nav file wasn't included, but it should only take less than 10 second to create. Enjoy!

EDIT 7/27/07:
Please redownload this, I have repackaged everything in a single BSP.
This is my first attempt at a decent map so feedback would be nice =)
